  "time_ut": 1658831828,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1\u0d9a \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0db7\u0dba \u0d9a\u0ddd\u0da7\u0dd2 10\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The daily loss of the train is more than 10 crores",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Dr. Bandula Gunawardena, Cabinet Spokesman, Minister of Transport, Highways and Mass Media said that the Railway Department is currently incurring a loss of more than 10 crores per day, and in the year 2021, its income was 260 crore rupees and the loss was 3,700 crore rupees.",
        "In that year, when the income was 260 crore rupees, 780 crore rupees were paid as employee salaries and wages. The minister also mentioned that 230 crores have to be paid as overtime allowances.",
        "The minister said this while addressing the press conference to inform the Cabinet decisions held today (26) at the Government Information Department.",
        "The minister said that in the year 2012, the revenue of the Railway Department was 480 crore rupees and the loss of that year was 3400 crore rupees.",
        "The minister said that the railway department has incurred a loss of a surprising amount due to the lack of income relative to the increase in expenditure for a long time and mentioned that the railway department is incurring a loss of around 4,000 crores per year.",
        "As a result, the train fares have been increased, but it is about 50 percent less compared to the bus fares, and it is a mistake for the station masters to take professional action saying that they cannot charge it.",
        "The minister said that when the price of fuel increased from 121 to 400 rupees, all the transport charges increased, and he said that it is not possible to run the train without increasing the fare, and if there is no money to get fuel, it will not be possible to run the train even if there are employees.",
        "The minister said that the fare for traveling from Kelaniya to Kollupitiya by train was 10 rupees and it has increased to 20 rupees.",
        "The minister also said that to travel the 420 km distance from Colombo to Jaffna by bus, 1683 rupees are charged and the train fare is only 580 rupees."
      ],
